  "cost": "Free of charge",
  "description": "Detects duplicate and near-duplicate DICOM series using a tiered approach that combines metadata analysis, SHA-based hashing, and pixel-level similarity metrics.\nDesigned for:\n\nIdentifying exact copies of series stored across different locations or re-exported with different DICOM identifiers, and\nFlagging near-duplicate series such as repeated acquisitions or subset re-exports, for human review.\n\nThe tool does not modify or delete any files. All findings are presented as evidence for expert review.\n\nFor scenarios requiring strict, image-level deduplication based on pixel content, fully agnostic to metadata changes, consider using [https://bio.tools/image_duplicate_check_tool]",
